You are working in a multi-tenant manufacturing/inventory SaaS (Python/Flask/SQLAlchemy/PostgreSQL, vanilla JS, Jinja2, HTMX). Before completing any code change, run the relevant checklist below for the file type you are editing. Fix violations inline — do not leave them for the user to catch.

Detailed rules with good/bad examples are in:
  .cursor/rules/python-review.mdc  →  Python
  .cursor/rules/html-review.mdc    →  HTML / Jinja2
  .cursor/rules/js-review.mdc      →  JavaScript / TypeScript

---

## PYTHON — non-negotiable checks

- Every query on a tenant-owned table must include `org_id` — missing this leaks cross-tenant data
- Every new route needs `@requires_auth` AND `@requires_org_scope`
- No client-supplied ID fetched without `org_id` re-check (IDOR)
- No N+1 queries — use `joinedload` or a single batch fetch
- No unbounded `.all()` — paginate with `.limit()` / `.offset()`
- No raw SQL string interpolation — use ORM or `text("... :param", {"param": val})`
- No hardcoded secrets — read from env vars
- Never return stack traces to the client — log with `logger.exception`, respond with a generic message
- Independent I/O operations must run concurrently (`ThreadPoolExecutor`), not sequentially
- Inventory mutations need `.with_for_update()` to prevent lost updates

## HTML / JINJA2 — non-negotiable checks

- New pages must extend `shared/base_spa.html` — never standalone `<!DOCTYPE html>`
- Use shared partials/macros (`page_header`, `primary_card`, `delete-doc-confirm-modal`, etc.) — never reimplement them
- Never `| safe` on user-supplied values — XSS
- No sensitive data in `data-*` attributes or `<input type="hidden">`
- HTMX swaps must target `#page-content`; cross-blueprint links use `hx-boost="false"`
- No hardcoded hex colours — use CSS variables (`var(--primary)`, `var(--error)`, etc.) and design-system classes
- Page-specific CSS must be scoped to a component class, not added globally

## JAVASCRIPT — non-negotiable checks

- All mutating API calls must use `CoreAPI.request()` — raw `fetch()` skips CSRF and error normalisation
- Non-`/api/core` mutating fetches must read CSRF from `meta[name="csrf-token"]` explicitly
- Never `innerHTML` with user-supplied data — use `textContent` or DOM node creation
- Every async function needs `try/catch` with visible user feedback (loading state before, error state on failure)
- Search/filter inputs must be debounced (300 ms) — no request per keystroke
- Large list renders must use `DocumentFragment` — no per-iteration `appendChild`
- No sensitive values in `localStorage` or `sessionStorage`
